records.addlTxt: Defendant Lily D Yonts in court.  Attorney Andrea N Winder in court for Lily D Yonts.  Attorney Lisa A. Riniker in court for State of Wisconsin. Per agreement, State moves to amend Cts 1 and 2 to 940.285(2)(a)1. State recommends 3 years probation with the following conditions: no contact with Victim, no unsupervised contact with anyone under the age of 18, counseling deemed appropriate by DOC, 30 days jail, court costs, and expungement. Court grants amendment. Court reviews plea questionnaire and finds defendant freely and knowingly waives rights. Defendant pleads not guilty to charges. Court accepts plea and finds defendant guilty. Court reviews rights lost due to felony conviction. State heard. Attorney Winder heard. Defendant heard. Court heard and orders 6 months jail with huber, court costs, and DNA- stayed. Court imposes 3 years probation with the following conditions: expungement, counseling deemed appropriate by DOC, not to have any contact with Victim #1, not to have any unsupervised contact with anyone under the age of 18, court costs, and to provide a DNA sample.
